    helpText: 'Having a safety plan prepared is essential for protecting yourself and your children if tensions escalate during divorce proceedings or if you\'re in an abusive relationship. Compile a list of emergency contacts, identify trusted friends or family who can provide temporary housing, and set aside emergency funds in a secure account only you can access. Keep copies of important documents, medications, and a few days of clothing in a safe location outside your home so you can access them quickly if needed.'
