    helpText: 'Business ownership adds significant complexity to divorce proceedings as business assets, income, and valuation methods must be carefully evaluated for equitable division. Collect all incorporation documents, partnership agreements, operating agreements, business tax returns, profit and loss statements, and any buy-sell agreements that may exist. Understanding the full scope of business interests and their value is crucial for protecting your ownership rights and ensuring fair compensation if the business needs to be divided or one spouse buys out the other.'
  }
];</parameter>
